      "span_text": "A T 1 -weighted inversion-recovery-prepared fast 3D gradient-echo sequence (BRAVO) was employed to obtain anatomical images of the whole brain of each subject. The acquisition parameters were: flip angle = 12°, inversion time = 400 ms, repetition time (TR) = 8.8 ms, echo time (TE) = 3.5 ms. The whole brain volume was covered at high-resolution using field-ofview = 240 × 192 × 175 mm [CITATION_1] and matrix 288 × 288 × 146 (i.e. voxel volume = 0.8 × 0.7 × 1.2 mm 3 , * 0.7 μl)."
